---
import Reading from "../layouts/Reading.astro";
import { REPO_URL, HUB_URL, VERSION } from "../config";
---

<Reading
  title="Examples · Vela"
  description="Recipes for common tasks against the Vela substrate. Real binary, real outputs."
  active="examples"
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">vela cookbook</p>
    <h1 class="page-head__title">Recipes.</h1>
    <p class="page-head__sub">
      Real CLI flows for the things you'll actually do. Every command runs against the
      vela {VERSION} binary; outputs are captured stdout. New to the substrate? Start with
      <a class="inline-link" href="/quickstart">/quickstart</a>.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="rcp">

    <nav class="rcp__toc" aria-label="On this page">
      <p class="rcp__toc-eyebrow">Recipes</p>
      <ol class="rcp__toc-list">
        <li><a href="#new-frontier">1 · Scaffold a new frontier</a></li>
        <li><a href="#manual-finding">2 · Add a finding manually</a></li>
        <li><a href="#sign">3 · Generate a key, register an actor, sign</a></li>
        <li><a href="#link">4 · Link two findings</a></li>
        <li><a href="#correction">5 · Record a Correction event</a></li>
        <li><a href="#publish">6 · Publish to the hub</a></li>
        <li><a href="#verify">7 · Verify a published frontier from disk</a></li>
        <li><a href="#mirror">8 · Mirror a hub locally</a></li>
        <li><a href="#scout">9 · Run an AI agent (Literature Scout)</a></li>
        <li><a href="#api">10 · Query the hub HTTP API</a></li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <!-- 1 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="new-frontier">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">1 · Scaffold a new frontier</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        A frontier is a named scope of findings. Use <code>vela frontier new</code> when you
        intend to publish; use <code>vela init</code> when you want a local <code>.vela/</code>
        repo for solo work.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela frontier new \
    --name "alzheimers-bbb" \
    --description "Blood-brain barrier delivery in Alzheimer's" \
    bbb.json

· frontier scaffolded frontier 'alzheimers-bbb' at bbb.json
  next steps:
    1. vela finding add bbb.json --assertion '...' --author 'reviewer:you' --apply
    2. vela sign generate-keypair --out keys
    3. vela actor add bbb.json reviewer:you --pubkey "$(cat keys/public.key)"
    4. vela registry publish bbb.json --owner reviewer:you --key keys/private.key --locator &lt;url&gt; --to {HUB_URL}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- 2 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="manual-finding">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">2 · Add a finding manually</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        Without <code>--apply</code>, the finding lands as a pending proposal in the inbox.
        With <code>--apply</code>, it becomes a canonical event.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela finding add bbb.json \
    --assertion "Focused ultrasound transiently opens the BBB in early-AD patients." \
    --type therapeutic \
    --evidence-type experimental \
    --doi "10.1038/s41591-024-XXXXX" \
    --author "reviewer:demo" \
    --confidence 0.55 \
    --apply

Finding proposal applied
  frontier: alzheimers-bbb
  finding:  vf_4c8a91d28e7b3712
  proposal: vpr_a3e7f12b9c4d8e15
  status:   applied
  event:    vev_8b3c194fd217ae62</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- 3 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="sign">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">3 · Generate a key, register an actor, sign</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        Three commands. The keypair lives at <code>keys/</code>; the actor record lives in
        the frontier; the signature is over canonical-JSON of each finding minus the
        <code>signature</code> field.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela sign generate-keypair --out keys
· generated keypair · keys
  public key: 88ccb43144e9e228c37566554845dcd4e1f5afd3fab3e10d23df551dcdd87041

$ vela actor add bbb.json reviewer:demo --pubkey "$(cat keys/public.key)"
· registered actor reviewer:demo (pubkey 88ccb43144e9e228)

$ vela sign apply bbb.json --private-key keys/private.key
· signed 1 findings in bbb.json</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- 4 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="link">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">4 · Link two findings</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        Typed edges between findings. Kinds: <code>supports</code>, <code>depends</code>,
        <code>contradicts</code>, <code>narrows</code>, <code>supersedes</code>. Cross-frontier
        targets use <code>vf_&lt;id&gt;@vfr_&lt;id&gt;</code> form once you've declared the
        dependency with <code>vela frontier add-dep</code>.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela link add bbb.json \
    --from vf_4c8a91d28e7b3712 \
    --to vf_b3a219c845f01e7d \
    --type supports

· link added: vf_4c8a91d… --supports--&gt; vf_b3a219c…</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- 5 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="correction">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">5 · Record a Correction event</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        A Correction supersedes an existing finding with a new content-addressed claim. The
        old finding is flagged <code>superseded</code>; both remain queryable; the new
        finding gets an auto-injected <code>supersedes</code> link back to the original.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela finding supersede bbb.json \
    --supersedes vf_4c8a91d28e7b3712 \
    --assertion "Focused ultrasound opens the BBB in APOE4-positive early-AD patients only." \
    --author "reviewer:demo" \
    --confidence 0.71 \
    --apply

Supersede applied
  old: vf_4c8a91d28e7b3712 (now flagged: superseded)
  new: vf_e2f9018d7a4b3c6e (auto-link: supersedes → vf_4c8a91d…)
  event: vev_c19a4f7d825b1e30</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- 6 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="publish">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">6 · Publish to the hub</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        The hub is dumb signed transport. <code>--locator</code> is the public URL where you
        serve the frontier file (S3, GitHub raw, your own server). The hub stores a signed
        manifest with the snapshot hash; clients verify locally on read.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela registry publish bbb.json \
    --owner reviewer:demo \
    --key keys/private.key \
    --locator https://your-host.example/bbb.json \
    --to {HUB_URL}

· publishing manifest to {HUB_URL.replace(/^https?:\/\//, '')}
· vfr_id: vfr_72f8019b3d4c8a1e
· snapshot_hash: 7a91...0c4d
· signed_publish_at: 2026-05-02T18:14:33Z
· status: ok</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- 7 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="verify">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">7 · Verify a published frontier from disk</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        Anyone can pull the frontier file, recompute the snapshot hash through any of the
        three reducer implementations, and check it matches the hub manifest. No trust in
        the hub required.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela registry pull vfr_72f8019b3d4c8a1e --to /tmp/pulled.json
· fetched manifest from {HUB_URL.replace(/^https?:\/\//, '')}
· locator: https://your-host.example/bbb.json
· hash check: 7a91...0c4d == 7a91...0c4d  ok
· wrote: /tmp/pulled.json

$ vela sign verify /tmp/pulled.json

  VELA · SIGN · VERIFY · /TMP/PULLED.JSON
  ····························································
  total findings:   1
  signed:           1
  unsigned:         0
  valid:            1
  invalid:          0</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- 8 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="mirror">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">8 · Mirror a hub locally</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        Pull a signed manifest from one hub and POST it verbatim to another. Both hubs validate
        the signature against the embedded <code>owner_pubkey</code>; mirroring is a no-op
        for authenticity. Use this for resilience, seeding a fresh hub, or hub-deployment
        smoke tests.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela registry mirror \
    --vfr-id vfr_72f8019b3d4c8a1e \
    --from {HUB_URL} \
    --to https://my-hub.example/

· pulled manifest from vela-hub.fly.dev (signature verified)
· posted to my-hub.example (signature re-verified, accepted)
· status: ok</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- 9 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="scout">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">9 · Run an AI agent (Literature Scout)</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        Vela's agent commands run an LLM-backed pipeline against a folder of source material
        and write the results back as <code>finding.add</code> proposals tagged with an
        <code>AgentRun</code> record. Reviewers accept proposals via the inbox; nothing
        becomes canonical without a signed accept.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ vela scout ./papers --frontier bbb.json --backend sonnet

Literature Scout · sonnet
  walking 12 PDFs in ./papers ...
  proposals: 38 candidate findings
  written:   bbb.json (proposals: 38, status: pending_review)
  inbox:     vela inbox bbb.json</code></pre>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        Adjacent agents: <code>vela compile-notes</code> (Markdown / Obsidian),
        <code>vela compile-code</code> (Jupyter / Python / R), <code>vela compile-data</code>
        (CSV / Parquet), <code>vela review-pending</code>, <code>vela find-tensions</code>,
        <code>vela plan-experiments</code>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- 10 -->
    <section class="rcp__r" id="api">
      <h2 class="rcp__r-title">10 · Query the hub HTTP API</h2>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        No authentication, no rate limit, CORS open. The signature is the bind.
      </p>
      <pre class="rcp__code"><code>$ curl {HUB_URL}/entries | jq .
{`{
  "entries": [
    {
      "vfr_id": "vfr_bd91...",
      "name": "Alzheimer's Therapeutics",
      "owner_actor_id": "reviewer:will-blair",
      "snapshot_hash": "f23b4aba17...",
      "signed_publish_at": "2026-04-27T18:32:01Z"
    },
    ...
  ]
}`}

$ curl {HUB_URL}/.well-known/vela
{`{
  "protocol_versions": [1],
  "signing_algorithms": ["ed25519-canonical-json-v1"],
  "admin": "ops@vela.science"
}`}</code></pre>
      <p class="rcp__r-line">
        Full API at <a class="inline-link" href="/sdk#http">/sdk § Hub HTTP API</a>; protocol
        details at <a class="inline-link" href="/spec">/spec</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

  </article>
</Reading>

<style>
  .rcp { max-width: 60rem; margin: 0 auto; }

  .rcp__toc {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-7);
    padding: 1.1rem 1.4rem;
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .rcp__toc-eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 76%, var(--ink-2));
  }
  .rcp__toc-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.4rem 1.4rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .rcp__toc-list { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .rcp__toc-list li { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .rcp__toc-list a {
    color: var(--ink-1);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 38%, transparent);
    transition: color 160ms var(--ease), border-bottom-color 160ms var(--ease);
  }
  .rcp__toc-list a:hover { color: var(--gold-ink); border-bottom-color: var(--gold-ink); }

  .rcp__r {
    padding-top: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--rhythm-block);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
  }
  .rcp__r-title {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 1.8vw, 1.35rem);
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    color: var(--ink-0);
    text-transform: none;
  }
  .rcp__r-line {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.96rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    max-width: 70ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .rcp__r-line code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.86em;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--ink-0);
  }
  .rcp__code {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.62;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }
  .rcp__code code { background: transparent; border: 0; padding: 0; font: inherit; color: inherit; }
  .inline-link {
    color: var(--ink-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 56%, transparent);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    transition: color 160ms var(--ease), text-decoration-color 160ms var(--ease);
  }
  .inline-link:hover { color: var(--gold-ink); text-decoration-color: var(--gold-ink); }
</style>
